<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1856,2025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1929,1953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">Notes.</emphasis>
Recently recorded by 
<bibRefCitation box="[548,783,1929,1953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125" refString="Berchi, G. M., Kment, P. &amp; Petrovici, M. (2012) First record of the backswimmer Notonecta meridionalis (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Notonectidae) in Romania. Travaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle &quot; Grigore Antipa &quot;, 55 (2), 217 - 220." type="journal article">
Berchi 
<emphasis box="[634,689,1929,1953]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[716,775,1929,1953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from south-western 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1132,1929,1953]" name="Romania" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">Romania</collectingCountry>
(Mehedinţi county). This second record confirms the occurrence of this species in the country. It was also rarely collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1365,1966,1990]" name="Hungary" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">Hungary</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Soos" pageId="4" pageNumber="125" refString="Soos, N., Boda, P. &amp; Csabai, Z. (2009) First confirmed occurrences of Notonecta maculata and N. meridionalis (Heteroptera: Notonectidae) in Hungary with notes, maps, and a key to the Notonecta species of Hungary. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 60, 67 - 78." type="journal article" year="2009">
Soós 
<emphasis box="[151,200,2001,2025]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[214,275,2001,2025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Aspects of the hemelytral coloration pattern and the paramere are illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[1181,1258,2001,2025]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1875,1898]" captionTargetBox="[222,1364,454,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[195,1392,429,1851]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Variability of hemelytral coloration pattern. 1 – 4 –– Notonecta glauca glauca Linnaeus, 1758, 5 –– Notonecta maculata Fabricius, 1794, 6 –– Notonecta meridionalis Poisson, 1923, 7 – 8 –– Notonecta viridis Delcourt, 1909 (1, 6, 7 –– Argeş county: Negreşti, 2, 8 –– Galaţi county: Cioräşti 3, 4 –– Timiş county: Dumbräviţa, 5 –– Suceava county: Clit). Photographs by Denis Copilaş – Ciocianu." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222212/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">
Figs. 
<number box="[1244,1258,2001,2025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1312,1342,2001,2025]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,525,548]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,182,503]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[153,1433,182,504]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Aspects of parameres. 9 –– Notonecta glauca glauca Linnaeus, 1758, 10 –– Notonecta maculata Fabricius, 1794, 11 –– Notonecta meridionalis Poisson, 1923, 12 –– Notonecta viridis Delcourt, 1909 (9, 11, 12 –– Argeş county: Negreşti, 10 –– Suceava county: Clit). Photographs by Denis Copilaş – Ciocianu." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222213/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="125">
<number box="[1312,1342,2001,2025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="125" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
